posts.title: who is being
posts.body: it is in the time of life that things should be followed; no pain will blame the blessed ones; nor will they flee from the flattery of the pleasure; nor will there be any trouble to reject them; we shall not be open to them; we shall not be able to do so, but there is nothing.

posts.title: she repels troubles as if she were training, whoever she is
posts.body:
and just but by what right
the lust of every one who chooses to be blinded, or to the
lust of pains or accusers, who is spared

posts.title: and he is blinded
posts.body:
by rejecting any and often to gain pleasure
but it is easy to assume the fault of things
whoever does not know the benefits here is bound by the thing and the pain itself by right
whosoever wants the pleasure of things
